    <string name="dialog_rules_title">How to Not Lose at Chess? ü§î</string>
    <string name="dialog_rules_body">The goal is to trap the opponent\'s king (not in a garage).\n\n
‚Ä¢ Pawn: The hardest worker. Moves forward, captures diagonally. If it reaches the end, it can become anyone (except a sales manager).\n
‚Ä¢ Rook: Like a tank, but only in straight lines.\n
‚Ä¢ Bishop: Moves diagonally. Always knows where the truth is.\n
‚Ä¢ Knight: Jumps in an ‚ÄúL‚Äù shape and ignores the rules (of all other pieces).\n
‚Ä¢ Queen: The universal soldier. Moves both straight and diagonally.\n
‚Ä¢ King: The main guy, but only moves one square. Apparently, his bodyguards can\'t keep up everywhere.\n\n
Castling: Like a backup. Move your king and rook to be safer.\n
En Passant: When a pawn moves past, but you can still capture it.\n\n
To make a move, click on a piece, then on a square. Good luck, grandmaster! üòâ</string>
